# AI Scripts for Perfect Tower II
***Click the Script name for source and more information.***

***Scripts are made and meant to be edited using the [external editor](https://d0sboots.github.io/perfect-tower/), unless otherwise noted.***

***Scripts use [Turbo Execute](https://github.com/Xenos6666/TPT2_scripts/blob/main/common/turbo_exec/README.md) unless they are playing golf or otherwise noted.***

***Setting `turbo.cycles.max` above what the script uses makes it run within a single frame.***

***If sctipts come in a bundle, only interact with the main one. Unless you wish to tinker around.***

***Most scripts depend on my [Lib](Lib.tpt2), so if you wish to build from source you need to import it into the external editor also.***

***Scripts can come in 3 flavours:***

***Perf(Up to 25 Actions, Best speed)***

***Norm(Up to 15 Actions, Usable by everyone)***

***Golf(Minimal Actions, Sacrifices speed and maybe some functionality)***

*Sidenote: If using a factory sctipt and rushing T8(or so) Belt then T5 Producer, it is possible to quickly upgrade all the ram and get 25 Actions*
# Mine
Mine all spots across all tabs repeatedly.

## [Mine.Perf](Mine/Perf.tpt2)
Mines all layers. Worst case takes 2419 turbo cycles.

`Ir.Mine.Perf 2 1 25`
```

```
## [Mine.Norm](Mine/Norm.tpt2)
Mines all layers. Worst case takes 3475 turbo cycles.

`Ir.Mine.Norm 2 1 15`
```

```
## [Mine.Golf](Mine/Golf.tpt2)
Misses the initial layer, fixable with an additional Action.

`Ir.Mine.Golf 2 1 5`
```

```
# Factory Scripts
Collection of scripts to make factory use a more streamlined experience.

## [Crusher](Factory/Crusher.Perf.tpt2)
Crushes all but cunfigurable number of ores constantly.

`Ir.Crusher.Perf 2 1 9`
```

```
## [Mixer](Factory/Mixer.Perf.tpt2)
Uptiers dust to try to keep a configurable ratio.

`Ir.Mixer.Perf 2 1 14`
```

```
## [Boiler](Factory/Boiler.Perf.tpt2)
Downtiers dust to try to keep a configurable ratio.

`Ir.Boiler.Perf 2 1 7`
```

```
## Trash
Pressing "T" deletes all selected tiers of all selected items.

### [Trash.Specific.Perf](Trash/Spcf.Perf.tpt2)
More control and faster compared to the Simple version. Edit using [external editor](https://d0sboots.github.io/perfect-tower/).

`Ir.Trash.Spcf.Perf 1 1 15`
```

```

### [Trash.Simple.Perf](Trash/Simple/Main.Perf.tpt2)
Simple to edit in-game.

`Ir.Trash.Smpl.Perf 1 1 12` `Ir.Trash.Smpl.Engn.Perf 0 0 14`
